[SN]TITLE[SN]
Attempted murder charge over Stockport hotel shooting

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with attempted murder after a woman was shot in a hotel.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 46-year-old was injured at the Britannia Hotel in Dialstone Lane, Offerton in Stockport, at about 02:20 GMT on Tuesday.
She suffered serious abdominal wounds and remains in a serious but stable condition in hospital.
David Andrew Jeffers, 47, of Berkley Terrace, Leeds, is due before Stockport Magistrates' Court on Saturday.
